<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880108-0021 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: CSX Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CSX </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   CSX Corp., Richmond, Va., said it is evaluating its oil and gas business and that it may consider selling its energy reserves.    A spokesman said several potential buyers have asked whether the oil and gas reserves are for sale. The company said it is conducting the review to see whether the oil and gas production business fits into CSX's long-term strategic objectives.    CSX is primarily a transportation concern. In 1987, oil and gas business generated revenue of $226.8 million, or about 2.8% of CSX's $8.04 billion total revenue. As of Dec. 31, 1986, CSX had oil and condensate reserves of 13.9 million barrels, and gas reserves of 346 billion cubic feet. </TEXT></DOC>